OFFICIAL DOCS LOG SPRING BOOT WITH SLEUTH : https://docs.spring.io/spring-cloud-sleuth/docs/3.0.3/reference/html/project-features.html#features-log-integration-json-logback
logging example : https://springframework.guru/using-logback-spring-boot/


1.Spring Boot use Logback for the default logger

2.SLF4j Log library is an interface we have used sl4j Library allowing us to plug in the desired logging 
framework at deployment time. (e.g. java.util.logging, logback, log4j)

3.Spring Boot team provides us a default configuration for Logback in the Spring Boot default Logback configuration file,  base.xml